asp 42 C F R Part 50 Subpart A The conference workshop program supports four to six events each year in collaboration with institutions scientific societies and institutional associations to explore various issues related to research integrity the responsible conduct of research and research misconduct The legal program provides interpretations of regulations and policies ORI conducts intramural and extramural studies on research misconduct and research integrity through in house projects contractors and a grant program to develop a knowledge base to guide its education and prevention efforts To assist institutions to effectively handle allegations of research misconduct ORI provides a Rapid Response Technical Assistance Program ORI also has fellow and intern programs to attract talented individuals to the research integrity effort horizontal line Questions suggestions about this web page mailto rnathan osophs dhhs gov Webmaster Updated February 15 2002 
